alex.mojaki.boxes.observers.change

Interface ChangeObserver<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChangePrinter, RequireBounds, TargetedChangeObserver, ThrowOnNull

    public interface ChangeObserver<T>
    A PowerBox can apply a list of these objects after the value of a box changes, typically to incur some side effect such as logging or to throw an exception if the value is invalid.
    See Also:
    PowerBox.set(Object), PowerBox.addChangeObserver(ChangeObserver[]), BoxFamily.addChangeObserver(ChangeObserver[])

    • Method Detail

      • onChange

        void onChange(PowerBox<T> box,
              T originalValue,
              T finalValue,
              T requestedValue)
        Take some action based on the values involved in the change. Called when the value of a PowerBox changes for zero or more of these objects.
        Parameters:
        box - the PowerBox whose value changed.
        originalValue - the value the box contained before the change.
        finalValue - the new value the box will have. In the case of PowerBox.set(Object), this is the final result of applying all ChangeMiddleware.
        requestedValue - the parameter of PowerBox.set(Object), or just the same as originalValue in the case of a mutation to a WrapperBox.
